				<div class='rssContent' style='text-align:left; color: black; font-size:11px;margin-bottom:10px;'><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: left;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-mgjs2ZnErok/TuRZ6g96Z_I/AAAAAAAAATM/jS6ULqmawK8/s1600/ghflag1.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-mgjs2ZnErok/TuRZ6g96Z_I/AAAAAAAAATM/jS6ULqmawK8/s1600/ghflag1.jpg" /></a>Anyone who dabbles in D&amp;D fantasy&nbsp;illustration should check out <a href="http://greyhawkery.blogspot.com/2013/01/new-contest-at-wizards.html" target="_blank">this contest</a> over at <em>Wizards</em>. Getting a small piece of art published in the reprint of the A-series, <em>Against the Slave Lords</em> hardback would be not only a personal triumph but it could also be a point of pride if one or more people from the <strong>Canonfire</strong> community can get&nbsp;credited in this book. Get in on this possibly once in a life time opportunity.</div></div>
